      "id": "f7cb8734_7a127391",
      "file_path": "k6-tests/ncmp/ncmp-kpi.js",
      "patchset_number": 4,
      "line": 193,
      "message": "No they don't cause the tests to fail, and we don't plot them either.\nWe really use them for debugging while writing tests, e.g. if you comment out custom summary function on line 214 and run the tests, you'll see these checks being printed out:\n\n     ✗ status equals 200\n      ↳  24% — ✓ 49 / ✗ 151\n\nWith this patch, we are now using the result of the checks to only record timings for successful operations.",
